    "title": {
      "rendered": "ATTN Nonprofits: New YouTube Channels Coming Early March 2013"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/hero_image-vflEKu2zL.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-12816\" alt=\"hero_image-vflEKu2zL\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/hero_image-vflEKu2zL-300x156.png?resize=300%2C156\" width=\"300\" height=\"156\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/hero_image-vflEKu2zL.png?resize=300%2C156&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/hero_image-vflEKu2zL.png?w=680&amp;ssl=1 680w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a>YouTube has begun rolling out a new YouTube Channel design entitled <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/onechannel\">One Channel</a> to a very small small group of YouTube users. A sitewide roll out is expected in early March. The new design offers much less customization, but enables more efficient browsing of your videos and the channels that you are subscribed to, and is more tailored for smartphone and tablet video watching. To prepare in advance for the new YouTube Channels, nonprofits will need to design a new banner. To keep it simple, YouTube has released new\u00a0<a href=\"http://support.google.com/youtube/bin/answer.py?hl=en&amp;answer=2972003&amp;topic=16630&amp;ctx=topic\">Channel Art Guidelines</a>\u00a0that indicate a banner that is in the &#8220;Safe Area&#8221; i.e., 1280 x 350 pixels,\u00a0will be visible on all devices: desktop, tablet, smartphone and TV.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>New YouTube One Channel Design :: <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/user/sortedfood\">Home View :: SORTED Food</a></strong><br />\nPlease note the ability to embed your website links in the lower right of your banner and the new video and subscription activity feed on the left side of the screen.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/user/sortedfood\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-11645\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"YouTube1\" src=\"http://nonprofitorgs.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/youtube1.png?w=600&#038;resize=600%2C335\" width=\"600\" height=\"335\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><br />\nNew YouTube One Channel Design ::\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/user/sortedfood/discussion\">Discussion View ::\u00a0SORTED Food<br />\n</a></strong><a href=\"http://mashable.com/2013/02/10/internet-trolls/\">Ignore the trolls</a>. YouTube has the worst of them.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/user/sortedfood/discussion\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-11647\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"YouTube2\" src=\"http://nonprofitorgs.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/youtube2.png?resize=600%2C333\" width=\"600\" height=\"333\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><br />\nNew YouTube One Channel Design ::\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/user/sortedfood/about\">About View ::\u00a0SORTED Food<br />\n</a></strong>Friends are back. They&#8217;ve been hidden for a couple of years.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://nonprofitorgs.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/youtube3.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-11648\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"YouTube3\" src=\"http://nonprofitorgs.files.wordpress.com/2013/02/youtube3.png?resize=600%2C347\" width=\"600\" height=\"347\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Related Link:</strong><br />\n<a href=\"http://www.diosacommunications.com/services/webinars.htm\">Webinar: How Nonprofits Can Successfully Use YouTube and Create Video Content for the Social Web</a></p>\n",
      "protected": false
    },
    "excerpt": {
